Code: InvalidParameterValue
Message: Invalid value given for parameter Login. Specify a valid parameter value.

The az sql server create command requires a valid --admin-user and --admin-password for SQL authentication.
Entra ID admin is set separately and does not replace these required parameters.
Update the command to include --admin-user and --admin-password (use secure environment variables or secrets).

Set SQLADMINUSER and SQLADMINPASSWORD environment variables before running the script.
Do not use Entra ID username/object ID for these parameters.
Example:

export SQLADMINUSER="sqladmin"
export SQLADMINPASSWORD="yourStrongPassword123!"

# Create SQL server
az sql server create \
    --name $serverName \
    --resource-group $resourceGroup \
    --location $location \
    --admin-user $SQLADMINUSER \
    --admin-password $SQLADMINPASSWORD

